methods.exportId:
Get the export ID.

:return: (io.deephaven.client.impl.ExportId) the export ID
methods.isReleased:
True if this has been released.

:return: (boolean) true if released
methods.newReference:
Creates a new reference export that has its own ownership and lifecycle. Must not be called after this
 export has been released.

:param listener: (io.deephaven.client.impl.ExportRequest.Listener) - the listener
:return: (io.deephaven.client.impl.Export) the new reference export
methods.pathId:
Get the path ID.

:return: (io.deephaven.client.impl.PathId) the path ID
methods.release:
Releases this export. May be called multiple times without adverse effect.

:return: boolean
methods.table:
The table spec.

:return: (io.deephaven.qst.table.TableSpec) the table spec
methods.ticketId:
Get the ticket ID.

:return: (io.deephaven.client.impl.TicketId) the ticket ID

text:
An export represents a server-side object that is being kept alive.

 
 Callers must maintain ownership of their exports, and close them when no longer needed.
